> Warhead: Not for now. There might be a hostile group. We'll wait for
> confirmation before we change to beast mode. For now, Drillbit,
> Nightshade, follow me. We advance 100 meters, Drillbit on the left,
> Night, you're on the right. Go!
>
> He starts running in a straight line. He stops about 100 meters
> farther.
>

{Nightshade}

    The fox moved as instructed taking note of the terrain making sure she
kept her eyes on the lead bot, she wasn't concerned about a hostile patrol
finding them. If the maxi ship was anything like the frigate they stole it'd
be just as much scrap. No they'd be organizing debating planning. Silly
notions of asking what each crew thought.

    Smiling as she advanced the distance she looked around at the plant
life. History painted this dirt ball as a livable planet but all this
organic garbage was in the way, while he new beast form was fitting for one
of her beauty she preferred her robotic form much more. Sighing she matched
positions with the other bots looking rather bored.
